The shepherd's crook is a common tool used by shepherds to guide and protect his flock. This stylized version represents a leader guiding and protecting his people.
This long, bronze staff seems polished despite it's age. One could wonder what purpose it's meant to serve.
Flails are tools commonly used by farmers to thresh grain. This stylized version of it represents a leader providing for his people.

More an axe than a sword, this long, curved weapon has proven to be amazingly powerful. 

Not only is this example still very sharp, but it's intricate designs are easily recognizable.

A dried-out body lies beneath the statue. Though obviously ancient, it's amazingly well-preserved, almost certainly do to the hot, dry atmosphere inside the crypt.

From the positioning of the body, one could guess the person was sacrificed in life.
He who enters here cross not this stone, for he who does shall suffer a thousand curses and beg not for his life, but for his death.
